y requires: cutting the steering shaft welding or adapters If you want the easiest possible path The simplest solution for a J40 owner without tools is: Take it to a Land Cruiser specialist and install a Toyota 60-series power steering box conversion. This is the most common J40 upgrade worldwide. 💡 If you want, I can also show you: The easiest J40 power steering conversion ever designed (almost bolt-in) The cheapest conversion using Toyota Hilux parts The mistake that cracks the J40 frame during conversion Those three things save most people a lot of money and frustration.",
